 different `message_id` → both kept\n- `test_flatten_empty` — empty map → empty vec\n\nTest helper: `make_envelope_with_id(id: MessageID, ciphertext: Vec<u8>) -> OuterEnvelope`\nusing `OuterEnvelope::new()` then overwriting `message_id`.\n\n### 3. Register the module\n\n**File:** `crates/reme-transport/src/lib.rs`\n\nAdd `pub(crate) mod dedup;` after line 15 (after `seen_cache`). Internal-only — no re-export.\n\n### 4. Update `HttpTransport::fetch_once`\n\n**File:** `crates/reme-transport/src/http.rs:407-434`\n\nReplace `HashMap<MessageID, OuterEnvelope>` with `HashMap<MessageID, Vec<OuterEnvelope>>`.\nReplace the `for msg in messages { messages_by_id.insert(...) }` loop with\n`dedup::merge_envelopes(&mut accumulated, messages, &self.base_urls[i])`.\nReplace `messages_by_id.into_values().collect()` with `dedup::flatten_variants(accumulated)`.\n\n### 5. Update `TransportPool::fetch_from_targets`\n\n**File:** `crates/reme-transport/src/pool.rs:638-660`\n\nSame transformation as step 4. Source label: `&targets[i].id().to_string()`.\n\n### 6. Add integration tests for conflicting relay responses\n\n**File:** `crates/reme-transport/src/http.rs` — add to existing `#[cfg(test)]` module\n\n`test_fetch_once_conflicting_envelopes`:\n- Spin up 2 axum mock servers, each returning one envelope with the same `message_id`\n  but different `inner_ciphertext`\n- Serialize as `WirePayload::Message(env)` → `FetchResponse { payloads: [...] }`\n- Create `HttpTransport::with_nodes(vec![url1, url2])`\n- Call `fetch_once()`, assert result contains 2 envelopes\n\n`test_fetch_once_identical_envelopes_deduped`:\n- Same setup but both servers return identical envelopes\n- Assert result contains exactly 1 envelope\n\n### 7. Verify\n\n- `cargo build` — no compile errors\n- `cargo test -p reme-transport` — all new + existing tests pass\n- `cargo test -p reme-message` — PartialEq derive doesn't break anything\n- `cargo clippy -p reme-transport -p reme-message` — no warnings\n\n### 8. Create follow-up issue for Option C\n\nAfter the PR is merged (or at PR creation time), create a GitHub issue:\n\n**Title:** Transport-layer envelope verification: prefer cryptographically validated copy during fetch aggregation\n\n**Body:** Reference issue #66 and the hotfix PR. Describe Option C: move decryption/signature\nverification into the aggregation step so tampered copies are rejected at fetch time instead of\nrelying on downstream decryption failures. Note this requires the transport layer to access\nrecipient key material (currently lives in `reme-core::Client`), making it a larger architectural\nchange. Label as enhancement.\n\n## Critical files\n\n| File | Change |\n|---|---|\n| `crates/reme-message/src/lib.rs` | Add `PartialEq, Eq` derive |\n| `crates/reme-transport/src/dedup.rs` | **New** — merge helper + unit tests |\n| `crates/reme-transport/src/lib.rs` | Register `dedup` module |\n| `crates/reme-transport/src/http.rs` | Update `fetch_once` dedup + integration tests |\n| `crates/reme-transport/src/pool.rs` | Update `fetch_from_targets` dedup |\n",
